250 g Ground Beef
100 g Bacon Strips
2 unit(s) Artisan Bun
3 unit(s) Russet Potato
½ cup Goat Cheese, crumbled
1 cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
4 tbsp Ketchup
14 g Zesty Garlic Blend
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
1 tbsp Whole Grain Mustard
1 unit(s) Lettuce
90 mL Dill Pickle, sliced
2 tbsp Italian Breadcrumbs
28 g Crispy Shallots
113 g Mushrooms
1 tbsp Oil*
0.19 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F. Wash and dry all produce.
Remove any brown spots from potatoes. Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch rounds.
To a parchment-lined baking sheet, add potatoes and 1 tbsp oil. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with half the Zesty Garlic Blend, salt and pepper. Toss to coat. Arrange in a single layer.
Roast in the middle of the oven for 25-28 min, until tender and golden. (NOTE: For 4 servings, roast in the middle and bottom of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium. Cut bacon strips in half, crosswise.
When hot, add bacon. (NOTE: For 4 servings, don't crowd the pan; cook bacon in batches, if needed.) Cook for 5-8 min, flipping occasionally, until crispy.**
Remove from heat. Using tongs, transfer bacon to a paper towel-lined plate. Set aside.
Remove and discard all but 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) bacon fat.

Meanwhile, thinly slice mushrooms.
In a small bowl, combine mayo and mustard.
Remove any damaged outer leaves of lettuce. Separate leaves. Tear into burger-sized pieces.
Drain pickles.
Reheat the pan with reserved bacon fat over medium-high.
When hot, add mushrooms. Cook for 5-6 min, stirring often and scraping up any browned bits, until mushrooms are tender.
Remove from heat, then season with salt and pepper. Transfer mushrooms to another small bowl.

To a medium bowl, add beef, breadcrumbs, remaining Zesty Garlic Blend and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) salt. Season with pepper, then combine.
Form mixture into 2 (4) 5-inch-wide patties.
Reheat the same pan (from step 3) over medium. When hot, add patties to the dry pan. Pan-fry for 4-5 min per side, until cooked through.**
Remove from heat. Sprinkle goat cheese or cheddar over patties. Cover and set aside for 2 min, until cheese melts.

Meanwhile, halve buns.
Arrange buns directly on the top rack of the oven, cut-sides up. Toast for 3-4 min, until browned. (TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!)
When potatoes are done, carefully remove baking sheet from the oven. Sprinkle any remaining cheddar over potatoes.
Return to oven and roast for 1-2 min, until cheese melts.

To servings bowls, add ketchup, bacon, crispy shallots, pickles and lettuce. Serve mustard-mayo sauce and sautéed mushrooms alongside.
Stack patties onto bottom buns, then divide between plates with top buns alongside.
Serve with potato coins and toppings for everyone to build their own plates. (TIP: Extra lettuce, mustard-mayo sauce, crumbled bacon and crispy shallots make a yummy side salad, if you like!)